1
00:00:01,170 --> 00:00:02,610
(Episode 113)

2
00:00:02,640 --> 00:00:04,910
Mom, you should put Bo Ra to bed.

3
00:00:06,040 --> 00:00:08,480
Bo Ra's sleepy, Grandma.

4
00:00:08,680 --> 00:00:12,250
My sweet Bo Ra, you're so cute.

5
00:00:13,120 --> 00:00:14,420
Bo Ra, let's go night-night.

6
00:00:15,190 --> 00:00:16,220
There you go.

7
00:00:16,650 --> 00:00:21,230
Jang Mi, shouldn't you get some rest too?
You've been through so much lately.

8
00:00:21,590 --> 00:00:24,760
I'm worried Grandfather will be lonely
all by himself.

9
00:00:25,130 --> 00:00:27,030
So I think I should go check on him.

10
00:00:29,070 --> 00:00:31,870
If Jang Mi's going, Suk Hee's going too.

11
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:33,770
Suk Hee will follow her.

12
00:00:33,940 --> 00:00:37,810
Mom, where are you going?
This is your home.

13
00:00:38,740 --> 00:00:42,110
Jang Mi might go to fill the void
Seo Rin left.

14
00:00:42,750 --> 00:00:44,180
Jang Mi is pretty.

15
00:00:46,180 --> 00:00:48,050
Suk Hee's head hurts.

16
00:00:48,720 --> 00:00:53,020
Mom, we need to take you to the doctor
for a check-up tomorrow. Okay?

17
00:01:07,010 --> 00:01:08,640
Chae Hwa Young!

18
00:01:10,410 --> 00:01:12,880
I swear I will rip you to shreds.

19
00:01:13,510 --> 00:01:16,510
I'll rip your organs out one by one...

20
00:01:16,750 --> 00:01:21,090
and make you die in agony, Chae Hwa Young!

21
00:01:23,090 --> 00:01:25,590
Doesn't it seem like Jung Suk Hee
has her mind back?

22
00:01:26,020 --> 00:01:28,490
Only someone in their right mind
could spew that kind of venom.

23
00:01:29,790 --> 00:01:31,730
It gives me the creeps
just thinking about it.

24
00:01:32,360 --> 00:01:33,360
I'm not so sure.

25
00:01:33,870 --> 00:01:35,870
She went right back to her old self
after that.

26
00:01:36,900 --> 00:01:39,670
She might have a moment of clarity
in an extreme situation,

27
00:01:39,770 --> 00:01:41,910
but it was probably just
a fleeting moment.

28
00:01:42,140 --> 00:01:44,040
Still, you never know.
Keep a close watch on her.

29
00:01:48,750 --> 00:01:50,920
Where have you been at this hour?

30
00:01:51,820 --> 00:01:53,920
I saw you hadn't left work yet,
so I waited for you.

31
00:01:55,620 --> 00:01:58,490
- What brings you two here?
- I asked you where you've been.

32
00:01:58,590 --> 00:02:00,490
I just came from meeting with Ma Seo Rin.

33
00:02:00,990 --> 00:02:03,290
- Is that what you wanted to hear?
- Get a grip, Kang Jun Ho.

34
00:02:03,800 --> 00:02:06,430
Have you forgotten
what I did to Oh Jang Mi's mother?

35
00:02:07,600 --> 00:02:10,570
Are you about to confess
that you ordered a hit on Jung Suk Hee?

36
00:02:10,770 --> 00:02:15,170
She fed you a few times as a kid,
and now you think she's some savior?

37
00:02:15,840 --> 00:02:19,080
Fine. I stole Seo Rin from Jung Suk Hee.

38
00:02:19,580 --> 00:02:20,810
I'm aware.

39
00:02:21,510 --> 00:02:23,880
You don't need to confess your sins
to me here.

40
00:02:23,950 --> 00:02:27,020
I also ordered Manager Lee
to get rid of...

41
00:02:27,020 --> 00:02:28,690
- Oh Jang Mi and Jung Suk Hee.
- Stop.

42
00:02:30,620 --> 00:02:32,460
- Stop it.
- You think that's it?

43
00:02:32,790 --> 00:02:36,530
- I even had her adoptive father...
- Shut up!

44
00:02:38,460 --> 00:02:40,030
- I told you to stop!
- Sit down.

45
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:44,340
Do you know how hard this is for me,
telling you the truth?

46
00:02:44,770 --> 00:02:48,940
What parent would show all their faults
for their child to see?

47
00:02:57,380 --> 00:02:58,880
So what's your point?

48
00:02:59,150 --> 00:03:01,190
After I handed Dream Group over to you,

49
00:03:02,150 --> 00:03:03,660
I was planning to confess everything.

50
00:03:04,890 --> 00:03:07,330
What does that have to do
with Jung Suk Hee?

51
00:03:07,490 --> 00:03:11,130
She means you must become much stronger
than you are now, General Manager Kang.

52
00:03:12,060 --> 00:03:16,430
If you won't give up on Oh Jang Mi,
you have to become more powerful.

53
00:03:16,530 --> 00:03:17,540
That's right.

54
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:21,410
If you want to win the girl,
you need to have power.

55
00:03:22,010 --> 00:03:24,240
What can a man with no ambition
possibly accomplish?

56
00:03:24,380 --> 00:03:27,780
Do I seem like I have no ambition?

57
00:03:28,380 --> 00:03:31,620
Do you really think
I want to marry Seo Rin purely for love?

58
00:03:35,220 --> 00:03:36,220
Manager Lee.

59
00:03:37,460 --> 00:03:41,430
I think it's time
we share everything with Jun Ho.

60
00:03:42,130 --> 00:03:44,830
Jun Ho, you really are my son.

61
00:04:09,590 --> 00:04:11,060
There's no CCTV here.

62
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:14,030
- What is this place?
- Security system deactivated.

63
00:04:14,090 --> 00:04:15,230
You'll see.

64
00:04:16,060 --> 00:04:18,660
I've wanted to show you
this place for a long time.

65
00:04:19,130 --> 00:04:23,000
But there were too many prying eyes,
so I had to be careful.

66
00:04:24,140 --> 00:04:25,370
I was waiting for the right moment.

67
00:04:58,240 --> 00:04:59,240
This place...

68
00:05:00,710 --> 00:05:01,710
What is this place?

69
00:05:07,610 --> 00:05:08,750
This is...

70
00:05:09,610 --> 00:05:12,350
where we will swallow Dream Group whole.

71
00:05:13,120 --> 00:05:14,450
A shell company.

72
00:05:37,610 --> 00:05:41,850
Unlike artwork, things like bonsai trees
and scholar's rocks don't have set prices.

73
00:05:41,980 --> 00:05:44,820
Their price is whatever we ask,
so they're perfect for cash transactions.

74
00:05:44,920 --> 00:05:47,920
- They're easy for money laundering.
- I see.

75
00:05:48,820 --> 00:05:50,490
It's useful for illicit currency exchange.

76
00:05:50,490 --> 00:05:52,590
It's also a perfect way
to avoid tax audits.

77
00:05:53,060 --> 00:05:56,890
Exactly. You're quick on the uptake,
just like my son should be.

78
00:05:57,330 --> 00:06:00,930
Now listen carefully to why
I showed you my treasure trove.

79
00:06:01,500 --> 00:06:03,270
You have to use Oh Jang Mi.

80
00:06:03,940 --> 00:06:05,700
Don't get caught up in some kind
of real love.

81
00:06:05,700 --> 00:06:09,040
Use her and focus only
on building your own kingdom.

82
00:06:09,440 --> 00:06:10,440
Kang Jun Ho.

83
00:06:14,010 --> 00:06:16,510
The patient, who was suffering
from dissociative amnesia,

84
00:06:17,150 --> 00:06:19,020
re-experienced the trauma,

85
00:06:19,220 --> 00:06:21,820
and it seems her brain's defense mechanism
has completely collapsed.

86
00:06:22,390 --> 00:06:24,360
Her defense mechanism collapsed?
What does that mean?

87
00:06:24,790 --> 00:06:26,190
Is that a good thing?

88
00:06:26,620 --> 00:06:29,690
The unbearable shock
of her daughter's death...

89
00:06:30,360 --> 00:06:31,700
has, paradoxically,

90
00:06:31,900 --> 00:06:35,070
shattered the subconscious prison
she'd been trapped in.

91
00:06:36,470 --> 00:06:37,770
Seo Rin...

92
00:06:38,670 --> 00:06:40,740
must have woken me up before she left.

93
00:06:48,110 --> 00:06:51,280
Tae Pyung, I'm here! It's me, San Wol.

94
00:06:51,950 --> 00:06:54,090
Hi, what can I get for you today?

95
00:06:54,220 --> 00:06:56,650
Let's see...

96
00:06:58,460 --> 00:06:59,960
Hello, this is Suk Hee's Side Dishes.

97
00:07:00,860 --> 00:07:02,560
The police station?

98
00:07:03,630 --> 00:07:06,760
Jung Suk Hee?
Yes, that's right. She's my mom.

99
00:07:07,970 --> 00:07:09,130
That's right.

100
00:07:09,630 --> 00:07:12,970
She had an appointment to register her DNA
for the Finding Missing Family program,

101
00:07:13,170 --> 00:07:14,270
and we completely forgot.

102
00:07:15,170 --> 00:07:18,680
We've had a death in the family recently,
so we've been overwhelmed.

103
00:07:18,880 --> 00:07:21,480
What? Finding Missing Family?

104
00:07:21,610 --> 00:07:25,350
I'll bring my mom to the station soon.

105
00:07:25,780 --> 00:07:26,780
Thank you.

106
00:07:29,820 --> 00:07:30,820
The police station?

107
00:07:31,420 --> 00:07:34,760
What's this about DNA registration?
Is it related to your mother?

108
00:07:34,930 --> 00:07:36,160
Do you mean Suk Hee?

109
00:07:36,460 --> 00:07:39,360
My mom was hoping to find her parents,

110
00:07:40,260 --> 00:07:43,370
so she'd scheduled an appointment
to register her DNA at the station.

111
00:07:43,570 --> 00:07:46,900
Oh, my. So, Suk Hee was an orphan?

112
00:07:47,210 --> 00:07:50,980
Oh, the poor thing.
She's had such a hard life.

113
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:56,210
Anyway, what side dishes look good today?

114
00:07:57,720 --> 00:07:58,820
Chae Hwa Young.

115
00:07:58,820 --> 00:08:00,080
(Director Ma Seo Rin)

116
00:08:00,590 --> 00:08:02,220
Why haven't you submitted
the analysis report?

117
00:08:02,820 --> 00:08:05,790
I told you to sort it by category
and upload it ages ago.

118
00:08:06,190 --> 00:08:08,990
Do you find it hard to focus
on an entry-level job at your age?

119
00:08:09,290 --> 00:08:11,160
There's a department meeting in two hours.

120
00:08:11,230 --> 00:08:14,070
I don't care how, but have it done
and bring it to the conference room.

121
00:08:14,330 --> 00:08:17,740
The board members will be there,
so no mistakes. Got it?

122
00:08:43,900 --> 00:08:45,060
Almost done.

123
00:08:45,660 --> 00:08:47,400
Oh Jang Mi, that insufferable witch.

124
00:08:47,970 --> 00:08:49,470
I need to get rid of her, and fast.

125
00:09:36,210 --> 00:09:37,210
There.

126
00:09:55,930 --> 00:09:56,970
Chae Hwa Young.

127
00:09:57,440 --> 00:10:00,370
Strangling you to death right now
wouldn't even be enough.

128
00:10:01,110 --> 00:10:02,240
You murderer.

129
00:10:02,910 --> 00:10:06,980
But I'm going to make it slow
and squeeze the life out of you.

130
00:10:14,790 --> 00:10:16,750
(Psychopath, murderer)

131
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:31,400
(Psychopath, murderer)

132
00:10:32,970 --> 00:10:36,070
(Murderer)

133
00:10:36,140 --> 00:10:37,140
What's going on?

134
00:10:37,540 --> 00:10:38,710
Seriously, who is it?

135
00:10:40,980 --> 00:10:43,610
- Hello?
- Ma'am, where are you?

136
00:10:44,220 --> 00:10:46,850
Hurry to the meeting.
Everyone is waiting for you.

137
00:10:48,090 --> 00:10:49,620
What? Are they?

138
00:10:50,190 --> 00:10:51,820
Okay, I'm on my way.

139
00:10:55,930 --> 00:10:58,130
(Murderer)

140
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:05,140
Sorry I'm late.

141
00:11:09,040 --> 00:11:10,310
What is...

142
00:11:11,240 --> 00:11:12,640
Oh my goodness.

143
00:11:13,140 --> 00:11:14,150
What is that?

144
00:11:14,480 --> 00:11:15,480
Oh my...

145
00:11:15,550 --> 00:11:17,450
(Psychopath, murderer)

146
00:11:18,150 --> 00:11:19,150
What is...

147
00:11:20,020 --> 00:11:22,590
I'm not that late.

148
00:11:23,320 --> 00:11:26,520
What's with all the shocked faces?
General Manager Kang, sit.

149
00:11:26,920 --> 00:11:29,060
Director Ma,
let's get the meeting started.

150
00:11:31,300 --> 00:11:34,330
Why are you walking around
with strange stamps all over your face?

151
00:11:35,770 --> 00:11:36,770
Stamps?

152
00:11:36,830 --> 00:11:39,100
You might want to
take a look at your face.

153
00:11:39,540 --> 00:11:40,840
What happened to her?

154
00:11:41,210 --> 00:11:42,910
Is there something on my face?

155
00:11:44,710 --> 00:11:45,710
You should look in a mirror.

156
00:11:48,010 --> 00:11:49,910
You should be thinking
about our stock price.

157
00:11:50,110 --> 00:11:52,120
My goodness, how embarrassing.

158
00:11:52,550 --> 00:11:55,850
- Let's pick this up another time.
- Seriously...

159
00:11:58,590 --> 00:11:59,590
Wait.

160
00:12:00,420 --> 00:12:03,560
What's going on?
What did I do to make them act like that?

161
00:12:03,890 --> 00:12:04,900
Unbelievable.

162
00:12:07,330 --> 00:12:09,170
"Murder..."

163
00:12:11,040 --> 00:12:12,040
(Psychopath)

164
00:12:12,270 --> 00:12:15,540
Who did this? Who stamped my face?
Who was it?

165
00:12:15,840 --> 00:12:16,840
Oh, no.

166
00:12:17,780 --> 00:12:20,540
Who did this? What is this?

167
00:12:20,910 --> 00:12:22,680
Oh my God, what is this?

168
00:12:23,650 --> 00:12:24,750
This is just for starters.

169
00:12:25,180 --> 00:12:28,450
Chae Hwa Young, I'm going to make
your life a living hell from now on.

170
00:12:28,950 --> 00:12:29,950
So you'd better be ready.

171
00:12:32,060 --> 00:12:33,060
Manager Lee.

172
00:12:33,520 --> 00:12:35,530
Round up everyone who went
into the break room today.

173
00:12:36,090 --> 00:12:39,560
Oh Jang Mi and Jin Hong Ju.
It must have been those two.

174
00:12:39,900 --> 00:12:40,970
I won't let them get away with this.

175
00:12:46,070 --> 00:12:48,270
It won't even come off.

176
00:12:52,110 --> 00:12:53,140
Seriously!

177
00:12:54,150 --> 00:12:55,580
(Psychopath)

178
00:12:56,150 --> 00:12:57,150
(Murderer)

179
00:12:59,320 --> 00:13:03,490
Mom, just like you said, Chae Hwa Young
was totally humiliated at work today.

180
00:13:03,550 --> 00:13:04,620
She was the talk of the town.

181
00:13:05,890 --> 00:13:09,590
But Mom,
where did you even get a stamp like this?

182
00:13:10,690 --> 00:13:14,170
If I had it my way,
I would've stamped her desk,

183
00:13:14,400 --> 00:13:16,800
her sofa, her picture frames,
and everything,

184
00:13:17,540 --> 00:13:19,670
but I was afraid I would get caught.
So after some thought,

185
00:13:20,070 --> 00:13:22,770
I decided to brand her face
like a scarlet letter.

186
00:13:23,470 --> 00:13:26,080
I had to let the world know somehow.

187
00:13:26,410 --> 00:13:29,810
But just as you'd hoped, Mom,
everyone was whispering.

188
00:13:30,350 --> 00:13:32,480
They were like,
"Why would it say 'murderer'?"

189
00:13:32,480 --> 00:13:34,420
And "Who could have done it?"

190
00:13:36,090 --> 00:13:38,620
So what was Chae Hwa Young's excuse?

191
00:13:39,760 --> 00:13:42,390
An excuse?
That would just look even more suspicious.

192
00:13:42,990 --> 00:13:46,830
She said it must've been a prank
from a disgruntled client.

193
00:13:47,130 --> 00:13:48,930
She just left it at that.

194
00:13:50,600 --> 00:13:52,240
I bet she was panicking.

195
00:13:52,740 --> 00:13:55,840
She was branded a murderer for all to see.

196
00:13:56,110 --> 00:13:59,340
By the way, Mom,
what kind of ink did you use?

197
00:13:59,840 --> 00:14:03,180
Chae Hwa Young was trying to scrub it off,
but it wouldn't budge.

198
00:14:03,250 --> 00:14:05,920
I used oil-based ink
so it wouldn't come off easily.

199
00:14:07,080 --> 00:14:10,420
I was tempted to just tattoo it on her.

200
00:14:11,360 --> 00:14:13,090
Now that she's had a taste
of what's to come,

201
00:14:13,790 --> 00:14:17,160
I'm going to take away everything she has.

202
00:14:23,700 --> 00:14:26,370
I told you I'd treat you to a nice meal.

203
00:14:26,540 --> 00:14:28,540
I've just been so busy.

204
00:14:29,540 --> 00:14:33,440
I've finally got some free time.
Please, have some too, Lawyer Han.

205
00:14:34,140 --> 00:14:37,050
I'd rather you use my first name.

206
00:14:37,580 --> 00:14:38,580
I see.

207
00:14:40,220 --> 00:14:41,690
Young Ja...

208
00:14:42,420 --> 00:14:43,490
I like the sound of that.

209
00:14:46,360 --> 00:14:48,990
I know, Kang Hyuk,
that you didn't agree...

210
00:14:49,730 --> 00:14:52,130
to this contract relationship lightly.

211
00:14:53,760 --> 00:14:55,070
For me, this time together...

212
00:14:55,500 --> 00:14:56,730
is therapeutic.

213
00:14:56,730 --> 00:14:58,370
It's something nice to look forward to.

214
00:14:58,770 --> 00:15:01,370
For now, I'd like us to just be
comfortable with each other, like friends.

215
00:15:02,610 --> 00:15:03,770
I also don't want Lawyer Han...

216
00:15:03,770 --> 00:15:06,440
I mean I don't want you...

217
00:15:07,480 --> 00:15:09,380
to get hurt, Young Ja.

218
00:15:10,280 --> 00:15:14,790
If you ever feel uncomfortable,
Kang Hyuk, you can end this contract.

219
00:15:14,850 --> 00:15:15,850
Okay?

220
00:15:18,560 --> 00:15:19,590
Han Young Ja.

221
00:15:23,590 --> 00:15:25,800
What do you two think you're doing here?

222
00:15:26,930 --> 00:15:29,600
- Can't you see we're having a meal?
- Han Young Ja.

223
00:15:30,470 --> 00:15:34,810
You dressed up and brought sandwiches
just to meet this bastard?

224
00:15:35,110 --> 00:15:37,540
What's wrong with doing this for a friend?

225
00:15:39,140 --> 00:15:40,140
A friend?

226
00:15:41,910 --> 00:15:43,180
What do you think you're doing?

227
00:15:43,880 --> 00:15:48,490
Manager Lee, who do you think you are,
hitting on my wife?

228
00:15:48,550 --> 00:15:49,850
Don't talk like that.

229
00:15:51,290 --> 00:15:53,920
- Don't insult Young Ja.
- What?

230
00:15:55,390 --> 00:15:58,600
- What was that?
- Do you really think she'd fall for that?

231
00:15:59,860 --> 00:16:00,860
If she were,

232
00:16:01,370 --> 00:16:04,370
she would've divorced you
and married a better man long ago.

233
00:16:04,970 --> 00:16:06,300
If anything, Young Ja...

234
00:16:06,870 --> 00:16:08,440
is the one trying to hold
her family together.

235
00:16:09,840 --> 00:16:11,410
"Young Ja?"

236
00:16:12,340 --> 00:16:16,250
Lee Kang Hyuk, who gives you the right
to call my wife by her name?

237
00:16:16,380 --> 00:16:17,380
Look who's talking.

238
00:16:18,580 --> 00:16:20,820
Did you forget what you did
right in front of your own wife?

239
00:16:20,820 --> 00:16:23,590
Hey, you punk,
you've really crossed the line.

240
00:16:23,650 --> 00:16:27,360
Stop it. Do you want to make a scene
like this at our sons' company?

241
00:16:27,590 --> 00:16:31,260
Do you want rumors that we're fighting
because we're both cheating?

242
00:16:31,330 --> 00:16:32,660
Just because your husband had an affair,

243
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:34,800
you're having one with her subordinate?

244
00:16:35,600 --> 00:16:37,430
We're clearly not in the same league.

245
00:16:40,040 --> 00:16:41,870
Don't you dare talk down about my man.

246
00:16:43,210 --> 00:16:44,410
Let's go, Kang Hyuk.

247
00:16:56,850 --> 00:16:58,060
"My man?"

248
00:16:59,320 --> 00:17:01,390
She's completely lost her mind.

249
00:17:02,490 --> 00:17:05,960
Han Young Ja, are you out of your mind?
Cheating on me right in front of my face?

250
00:17:06,200 --> 00:17:10,200
- Even if I did, I'm not as dirty as you.
- "Dirty?"

251
00:17:10,770 --> 00:17:13,000
You're the one who's dirty.

252
00:17:13,440 --> 00:17:15,840
Do you know...

253
00:17:15,840 --> 00:17:19,440
I've had to walk on eggshells
around you for over 35 years?

254
00:17:19,440 --> 00:17:22,010
You walked on eggshells around me?

255
00:17:23,010 --> 00:17:24,420
You've got to be kidding me.

256
00:17:24,850 --> 00:17:29,020
Speaking of which, when you found out
you were infertile and were falling apart,

257
00:17:29,020 --> 00:17:30,220
who was it that comforted you?

258
00:17:30,520 --> 00:17:33,920
I was the one who comforted you
and suggested we adopt.

259
00:17:34,190 --> 00:17:37,900
When we adopted Baek Ho and Jun Ho,
what did you say to me?

260
00:17:38,060 --> 00:17:40,760
You said, thank you
for making us a real family.

261
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:45,770
You said we'd raise our boys as our own,
even though we didn't give birth to them.

262
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:49,110
- You said that yourself, didn't you?
- So what?

263
00:17:49,410 --> 00:17:52,840
Are you trying to blame me now
for adopting Baek Ho and Jun Ho?

264
00:17:52,910 --> 00:17:56,150
After all that, are you happy now
that you're destroying our family?

265
00:17:58,820 --> 00:17:59,820
Mom.

266
00:18:02,320 --> 00:18:03,320
Hey...

267
00:18:04,920 --> 00:18:05,920
Baek Ho.

268
00:18:07,190 --> 00:18:08,260
Then does that mean...

269
00:18:09,890 --> 00:18:11,700
I'm not your real son?

270
00:18:13,300 --> 00:18:15,470
No, of course not.

271
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:17,000
No.

272
00:18:17,770 --> 00:18:18,770
Why would say that?

273
00:18:19,770 --> 00:18:22,270
No matter what anyone says,
you are my son.

274
00:18:22,270 --> 00:18:23,440
You are my son.

275
00:18:48,270 --> 00:18:49,330
Just tell me...

276
00:18:50,230 --> 00:18:51,240
the truth.

277
00:18:52,070 --> 00:18:54,300
Baek Ho, it's just...

278
00:18:54,970 --> 00:18:58,510
Baek Ho, you're an adult now.
You have a right to know the truth.

279
00:18:58,710 --> 00:18:59,710
Was I really...

280
00:19:00,640 --> 00:19:01,810
adopted?

281
00:19:03,880 --> 00:19:05,180
When was I adopted?

282
00:19:09,390 --> 00:19:10,590
I can't believe this.

283
00:19:11,190 --> 00:19:12,360
Wait, so you're really...

284
00:19:13,460 --> 00:19:15,090
not my birth mother?

285
00:19:15,430 --> 00:19:17,590
What does that matter now?

286
00:19:18,600 --> 00:19:20,160
You're my son.

287
00:19:21,400 --> 00:19:23,670
I may not have given birth to you,

288
00:19:24,230 --> 00:19:27,000
but you're the son I raised from birth.

289
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:28,040
Why...

290
00:19:29,710 --> 00:19:33,580
- Why didn't you tell me?
- You know now, don't you?

291
00:19:34,040 --> 00:19:36,710
Are you really going to grill us
about why we never told you?

292
00:19:38,020 --> 00:19:39,380
Will you stop it!

293
00:19:40,380 --> 00:19:42,950
How can you say that when he's in shock?

294
00:19:42,950 --> 00:19:46,690
I never once imagined...

295
00:19:46,890 --> 00:19:48,360
I wasn't your real son.

296
00:19:49,590 --> 00:19:50,660
And now...

297
00:19:51,960 --> 00:19:53,300
How am I supposed to process this?

298
00:19:53,730 --> 00:19:55,200
What are you, ten years old?

299
00:19:55,830 --> 00:19:58,640
You're old enough to get married
and have kids.

300
00:19:59,070 --> 00:20:02,010
What's the big shock? It's simple.

301
00:20:02,310 --> 00:20:03,310
You...

302
00:20:03,910 --> 00:20:08,450
are Han Young Ja and Kang Nam Bong's son.
Nothing has changed.

303
00:20:08,710 --> 00:20:11,820
Your dad is right about that, Baek Ho.

304
00:20:12,180 --> 00:20:15,750
I'm so, so sorry
you had to find out like this.

305
00:20:16,220 --> 00:20:17,320
I always meant...

306
00:20:17,990 --> 00:20:20,120
to tell you eventually.

307
00:20:20,120 --> 00:20:21,390
But...

308
00:20:21,730 --> 00:20:23,630
I just didn't have the courage.

309
00:20:24,730 --> 00:20:27,460
I was afraid that you'd push me away too.

310
00:20:28,330 --> 00:20:29,570
I was terrified.

311
00:20:31,740 --> 00:20:32,740
All right.

312
00:20:34,270 --> 00:20:35,810
That's all I can handle for today.

313
00:20:49,650 --> 00:20:51,190
This is all your fault, Kang Nam Bong.

314
00:20:51,520 --> 00:20:54,560
If you'd been a proper head of the family,
this wouldn't have happened!

315
00:20:55,690 --> 00:20:58,460
I'm so upset. Now that Baek Ho knows...

316
00:20:59,400 --> 00:21:01,000
What's going to happen to Baek Ho?

317
00:21:08,240 --> 00:21:11,210
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

318
00:21:13,210 --> 00:21:14,280
Baek Ho.

319
00:21:15,750 --> 00:21:16,850
What's wrong?

320
00:21:17,450 --> 00:21:20,350
No. I just missed you, Jang Mi.

321
00:21:20,680 --> 00:21:23,150
No, really, what is it?

322
00:21:27,420 --> 00:21:28,430
Baek Ho.

323
00:21:28,730 --> 00:21:29,730
Just for a moment.

324
00:21:30,630 --> 00:21:31,760
Let's just stay like this.

325
00:21:33,330 --> 00:21:34,330
Baek Ho.

326
00:21:34,930 --> 00:21:37,200
- What's wrong?
- Jang Mi.

327
00:21:38,270 --> 00:21:39,770
No matter what happens to me,

328
00:21:40,240 --> 00:21:41,540
your feelings for me won't change, right?

329
00:21:41,810 --> 00:21:44,910
Of course not.
Don't you be the one to change your mind.

330
00:21:46,180 --> 00:21:47,180
Right now...

331
00:21:48,480 --> 00:21:49,750
I feel so incredibly lonely.

332
00:21:54,720 --> 00:21:55,790
All of a sudden,

333
00:21:57,590 --> 00:21:59,860
it feels like every light in the world
went out,

334
00:22:02,160 --> 00:22:03,990
and I feel so hollow inside.

335
00:22:05,060 --> 00:22:07,830
Talk to me. Whatever it is, I can help.

336
00:22:08,900 --> 00:22:11,500
All I need is for you to recharge me.

337
00:22:12,840 --> 00:22:14,470
You're my light, after all.

338
00:22:15,510 --> 00:22:16,510
There's...

339
00:22:17,170 --> 00:22:19,380
something you can't tell me, isn't there?

340
00:22:22,150 --> 00:22:23,150
Baek Ho.

341
00:22:25,220 --> 00:22:26,220
Just...

342
00:22:26,850 --> 00:22:29,420
don't forget that I'm always on your side.

343
00:22:31,420 --> 00:22:33,490
Having you here by my side...

344
00:22:34,930 --> 00:22:36,230
is such a relief.

345
00:22:38,330 --> 00:22:39,660
Thank you, Jang Mi.

346
00:22:55,210 --> 00:22:56,450
Jung Suk Hee? What are you doing here?

347
00:22:56,850 --> 00:22:59,180
What business do you have here?
You’ve really ruined the mood.

348
00:22:59,680 --> 00:23:01,520
Mom, say hi.

349
00:23:02,120 --> 00:23:03,290
You thief!

350
00:23:03,650 --> 00:23:05,620
- A thief, Chae Hwa Young!
- Jung Suk Hee!

351
00:23:05,890 --> 00:23:08,090
I asked you what you're doing here!

352
00:23:08,190 --> 00:23:10,360
Why are you yelling?
You're scaring my mom.

353
00:23:11,130 --> 00:23:14,000
Hey. I gave my permission.

354
00:23:14,330 --> 00:23:17,730
- Your permission?
- Grandfather's lonely since Seo Rin left,

355
00:23:18,400 --> 00:23:19,970
so he asked me to move in.

356
00:23:19,970 --> 00:23:22,240
Mom came here with me
since she's always checking on me.

357
00:23:22,740 --> 00:23:23,740
What?

358
00:23:24,010 --> 00:23:26,380
As it turns out,
Geum Soon had to take a leave,

359
00:23:26,380 --> 00:23:28,580
so she's here to help cook.

360
00:23:28,650 --> 00:23:30,810
I'm a good cook. My food is yummy.

361
00:23:32,120 --> 00:23:34,180
I like the twisted donut old lady.

362
00:23:34,650 --> 00:23:38,790
My goodness, Suk Hee.
"Old lady" is a bit much, don't you think?

363
00:23:38,860 --> 00:23:39,860
Father.

364
00:23:40,920 --> 00:23:42,290
That is absolutely out of the question.

365
00:23:42,590 --> 00:23:44,690
You of all people know how things are
between me and her.

366
00:23:45,130 --> 00:23:46,160
She can't be here, Father.

367
00:23:46,330 --> 00:23:48,400
We're mortal enemies.

368
00:23:48,830 --> 00:23:51,000
You just had to go and kill my Seo Rin.

369
00:23:51,300 --> 00:23:53,700
It'll only be fair
when you die by my hand, too.

370
00:23:55,740 --> 00:23:58,640
Thief! Chae Hwa Young is a thief!

371
00:23:58,980 --> 00:24:01,750
See? She'll be like this
every single time she sees me.

372
00:24:01,880 --> 00:24:04,450
How can I live with someone like that?

373
00:24:04,450 --> 00:24:06,450
And she's Chairman Ma's daughter.

374
00:24:06,950 --> 00:24:09,350
If she stays here,
the truth will come out.

375
00:24:09,350 --> 00:24:10,750
I can't let that happen.

376
00:24:10,890 --> 00:24:14,360
You did steal Seo Rin,
so she's not wrong to call you a thief.

377
00:24:14,420 --> 00:24:15,430
Yeom San Wol!

378
00:24:16,290 --> 00:24:18,200
My mom isn't going to be living here.

379
00:24:18,760 --> 00:24:20,300
She says she likes our house better.

380
00:24:20,900 --> 00:24:24,230
Suk Hee is going home.
Suk Hee has a home, too.

381
00:24:24,370 --> 00:24:27,140
What other joy do I have left at my age?

382
00:24:28,510 --> 00:24:33,040
I'm not giving up on Jang Mi.
If you don't like it, you can leave.

383
00:24:33,580 --> 00:24:34,780
Are you telling me to leave?

384
00:24:35,610 --> 00:24:37,510
Are you kicking me out again?

385
00:24:38,250 --> 00:24:39,550
That's not happening.

386
00:24:39,550 --> 00:24:42,890
I can’t give up the 30 years
I’ve put into this family.

387
00:24:42,890 --> 00:24:44,150
No, I won't.

388
00:24:46,890 --> 00:24:48,020
Why is she...

389
00:24:48,860 --> 00:24:51,160
How could she be so ungrateful?

390
00:24:55,700 --> 00:24:58,470
I need you to focus on your work
for the company.

391
00:24:59,140 --> 00:25:02,040
And keep a close eye on Chae Hwa Young
to see if she's up to no good.

392
00:25:03,610 --> 00:25:06,740
Secretary Kim will investigate
Seo Rin's case.

393
00:25:07,010 --> 00:25:10,280
Grandfather, you can focus
on finding my aunt.

394
00:25:10,650 --> 00:25:13,580
Baek Ho and I are also looking into
what happened with Seo Rin.

395
00:25:14,750 --> 00:25:16,390
Thank you, Jang Mi.

396
00:25:17,390 --> 00:25:20,490
You must have been so hurt by me, right?

397
00:25:22,460 --> 00:25:25,800
I'll get your name back for you soon.
Just wait a little longer.

398
00:25:26,060 --> 00:25:27,700
I'm the one who started all of this.

399
00:25:28,300 --> 00:25:30,530
So it's only right
that I see it through to the end.

400
00:25:38,510 --> 00:25:42,050
There must be a reason Chae Hwa Young
felt she had to kill Seo Rin.

401
00:25:42,550 --> 00:25:43,750
I need to find out what it is.

402
00:25:44,250 --> 00:25:48,150
The terrible secret
that made her silence Seo Rin.

403
00:25:48,490 --> 00:25:49,550
What could it be?

404
00:26:06,400 --> 00:26:08,940
Looks like there's something in here.

405
00:26:11,140 --> 00:26:12,680
Jung Suk Hee moved in?

406
00:26:13,180 --> 00:26:14,910
Yes. Just my luck.

407
00:26:15,910 --> 00:26:17,110
This might actually be for the best.

408
00:26:17,480 --> 00:26:19,280
It's better to keep her close
and watch her.

409
00:26:19,280 --> 00:26:20,280
You think so?

410
00:26:20,920 --> 00:26:24,020
Still, the fact that Jung Suk Hee
is Ma Eun Hye really bothers me.

411
00:26:24,790 --> 00:26:27,920
If Chairman Ma ever catches on...

412
00:26:28,490 --> 00:26:30,360
(Chang)

413
00:26:45,880 --> 00:26:48,110
Get the car. I need to get home right now.

414
00:26:48,450 --> 00:26:50,210
- What?
- The necklace.

415
00:26:50,650 --> 00:26:53,250
Jung Suk Hee's necklace
is in my vanity drawer.

416
00:26:53,980 --> 00:26:56,150
If Jung Suk Hee happens to see that...

417
00:26:57,350 --> 00:26:58,560
It's all over.

418
00:27:33,420 --> 00:27:37,760
This is the newborn baby jacket
I got for Seo Rin.

419
00:28:40,620 --> 00:28:42,330
(The First Man)

420
00:28:42,390 --> 00:28:45,760
I heard whoever left you at the orphanage
also left this.

421
00:28:46,060 --> 00:28:48,730
But I feel like I've seen this crest
somewhere before.

422
00:28:48,970 --> 00:28:51,270
The woman you love, Oh Jang Mi, is dead.

423
00:28:52,140 --> 00:28:53,940
Are you still that delusional?

424
00:28:54,200 --> 00:28:55,970
We got married.
We're a married couple now!

425
00:28:56,470 --> 00:28:59,680
Jung Suk Hee knows grapefruit is bad
for high blood pressure.

426
00:28:59,740 --> 00:29:01,440
She was trying to kill the Chairman.

427
00:29:01,680 --> 00:29:03,680
If the Chairman feels he's in danger,

428
00:29:03,680 --> 00:29:05,750
he'll never want
to see Jung Suk Hee again.

429
00:29:06,880 --> 00:29:08,890
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
